[2026-07-22T18:34:24.654Z] Possible reasons for having these kinds of units are:
[2026-07-22T18:34:24.655Z] • A unit may be statically enabled by being symlinked from another unit's
[2026-07-22T18:34:24.655Z]   .wants/, .requires/, or .upholds/ directory.
[2026-07-22T18:34:24.655Z] • A unit's purpose may be to act as a helper for some other unit which has
[2026-07-22T18:34:24.655Z]   a requirement dependency on it.
[2026-07-22T18:34:24.655Z] • A unit may be started when needed via activation (socket, path, timer,
[2026-07-22T18:34:24.655Z]   D-Bus, udev, scripted systemctl call, ...).
[2026-07-22T18:34:24.655Z] • In case of template units, the unit is meant to be enabled with some
[2026-07-22T18:34:24.655Z]   instance name specified.
